================================================================================
  1. DATA COLLECTION OVERVIEW
================================================================================

  UNJYNX collects the minimum data necessary to provide its core functionality.
  Our backend is self-hosted -- we do not use Firebase, Supabase, or any BaaS
  platform that processes data on third-party infrastructure outside our control.

  DATA COLLECTED:

  +-------------------------+----------+----------+--------------------------+
  | Data Type               | Required | Optional | Purpose                  |
  +-------------------------+----------+----------+--------------------------+
  | Name / Display Name     | Yes      |          | Profile, team display    |
  | Email Address           | Yes      |          | Auth, account recovery   |
  | Password (hashed)       | Yes      |          | Authentication           |
  | Profile Photo           |          | Yes      | User profile             |
  | Phone Number            |          | Yes      | SMS/WhatsApp OTP verify  |
  | Task Content            | Yes      |          | Core app functionality   |
  | Project Names           | Yes      |          | Core app functionality   |
  | Due Dates & Schedules   | Yes      |          | Reminder delivery        |
  | Notification Prefs      | Yes      |          | Channel routing          |
  | Device Push Token       | Yes      |          | Push notifications       |
  | Device Model & OS       | Yes      |          | Crash reporting, compat  |
  | App Version             | Yes      |          | Support, compatibility   |
  | IP Address              | Yes      |          | Rate limiting, security  |
  | Timezone                | Yes      |          | Correct reminder timing  |
  | Usage Analytics         |          | Yes      | Product improvement      |
  | Crash Logs              | Yes      |          | Bug fixing, stability    |
  +-------------------------+----------+----------+--------------------------+

================================================================================
  2. DATA SHARING
================================================================================

  UNJYNX DOES NOT SELL USER DATA. EVER.

  DATA SHARED WITH THIRD PARTIES:

  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | Third Party             | Data Shared  | Purpose                           |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | Sentry                  | Crash logs,  | Error tracking and crash          |
  |                         | device info, | reporting. No task content is     |
  |                         | stack traces | sent. Anonymized where possible.  |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | PostHog                 | Anonymized   | Product analytics. All user IDs   |
  |                         | events,      | are anonymized. No PII is sent.   |
  |                         | feature usage| Users can opt out in Settings.    |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | RevenueCat              | User ID,     | Subscription management and       |
  |                         | purchase     | billing via App Store / Play      |
  |                         | receipts     | Store. Required for IAP.          |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | Gupshup (WhatsApp BSP)  | Phone number,| WhatsApp message delivery.        |
  |                         | message text | Only when user opts in.           |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | MSG91 (SMS provider)    | Phone number,| SMS delivery. Only when user      |
  |                         | message text | verifies and opts in.             |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | SendGrid (Email)        | Email addr,  | Email reminder delivery.          |
  |                         | message text | Only when user opts in.           |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+
  | FCM (Firebase Cloud     | Device token | Push notification delivery only.  |
  | Messaging)              |              | No task content in FCM payload.   |
  +-------------------------+--------------+-----------------------------------+

  IMPORTANT DISTINCTIONS:
  - Task content is ONLY sent to messaging channels the user has explicitly
    enabled and verified (via OTP for WhatsApp/SMS)
  - Analytics (PostHog) receives NO task content, NO names, NO emails
  - Crash reporting (Sentry) may include stack traces but NO user task data
  - Team workspace data is shared ONLY with explicitly invited team members

================================================================================
  3. ENCRYPTION
================================================================================

  IN TRANSIT:
  - TLS 1.3 enforced on all API endpoints
  - HSTS (HTTP Strict Transport Security) enabled
  - Certificate pinning in mobile app (production builds)
  - WebSocket connections use WSS (TLS-encrypted)

  AT REST:
  - PostgreSQL: encrypted tablespace (AES-256)
  - MinIO object storage: server-side encryption (SSE-S3)
  - Backups: encrypted with AES-256 before upload
  - Valkey (Redis-compatible): in-memory only, no disk persistence of
    sensitive data (OTPs expire in 60s, sessions in Logto)

  SECRETS:
  - All API keys, tokens, and credentials stored in environment variables
  - Never committed to source code
  - Rotated on any suspected exposure

================================================================================
  4. DATA DELETION
================================================================================

  USER-INITIATED DELETION:
  - Settings > Privacy > Delete My Account
  - Triggers a 30-day grace period (user can cancel deletion during this time)
  - After 30 days, ALL user data is permanently and irreversibly deleted:
    * Profile information
    * All tasks, projects, subtasks, comments
    * Notification preferences and channel connections
    * Progress history, streaks, analytics
    * Team memberships (user is removed from all teams)
    * Push tokens and channel verification data
  - Confirmation email sent upon deletion request and upon final deletion

  ADMIN-INITIATED DELETION:
  - Admin can trigger immediate deletion for policy violations
  - Same comprehensive data removal as user-initiated

  WHAT PERSISTS AFTER DELETION:
  - Anonymized, aggregated analytics (cannot be traced back to individual)
  - Audit logs retained for 90 days (legal/compliance requirement)
  - Billing records retained per tax law requirements (7 years in India)

  DELETION OF CHANNEL DATA:
  - When a user disconnects a channel (e.g., removes WhatsApp):
    * OTP verification data deleted immediately
    * Phone number removed from our database
    * Unsubscribe request sent to messaging provider (Gupshup, MSG91, etc.)
    * Delivery history retained for 30 days, then purged

================================================================================
  5. DATA RETENTION
================================================================================

  +---------------------------+-----------------------------------------------+
  | Data Category             | Retention Policy                              |
  +---------------------------+-----------------------------------------------+
  | Active account data       | Retained while account is active              |
  | Completed tasks           | Retained for progress history (user can       |
  |                           | manually delete individual tasks)              |
  | Crash logs (Sentry)       | 90 days                                       |
  | Analytics events          | 12 months (anonymized after 30 days)          |
  | OTP codes                 | 60 seconds (auto-expire)                      |
  | Session tokens            | 7 days (refresh), 15 minutes (access)         |
  | Delivery attempt logs     | 90 days                                       |
  | Deleted account data      | 30-day grace period, then permanent deletion  |
  | Billing records           | 7 years (Indian tax law compliance)           |
  | Audit logs                | 90 days                                       |
  +---------------------------+-----------------------------------------------+

================================================================================
  6. THIRD-PARTY SDK DETAILS
================================================================================

  SENTRY (Crash Reporting)
  - Purpose: Real-time error tracking and crash reporting
  - Data sent: stack traces, device model, OS version, app version, breadcrumbs
  - Data NOT sent: task content, user names, email addresses
  - Privacy: https://sentry.io/privacy/
  - Data processing: EU/US servers (configurable)
  - User control: Cannot opt out (essential for app stability)

  POSTHOG (Product Analytics)
  - Purpose: Understanding feature usage to improve the product
  - Data sent: anonymized user ID, feature events, screen views, app version
  - Data NOT sent: task content, personal information, email, name
  - Privacy: https://posthog.com/privacy
  - Data processing: Self-hosted instance (same infrastructure as backend)
  - User control: Can opt out in Settings > Privacy > Analytics

  REVENUECAT (Subscription Management)
  - Purpose: Managing in-app purchases and subscription state
  - Data sent: anonymous app user ID, purchase receipts, subscription status
  - Data NOT sent: task content, personal information beyond billing
  - Privacy: https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy
  - Data processing: US servers
  - User control: Required for paid features, cannot opt out if subscribed

  FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging)
  - Purpose: Delivering push notifications to Android and iOS devices
  - Data sent: device push token, notification title/body
  - Data NOT sent: full task details (notification body is a summary only)
  - Privacy: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
  - Note: FCM is used ONLY for push delivery. No other Firebase services
    are used. No Firebase Analytics, no Firestore, no Firebase Auth.

