================================================================================
  9. DPDP ACT 2023 COMPLIANCE STATEMENT
================================================================================

  UNJYNX by METAminds complies with the Digital Personal Data Protection Act,
  2023 (India) as follows:

  LAWFUL PURPOSE & CONSENT:
  - Personal data is processed only for the purpose of providing task
    management and reminder services, as consented to by the user upon
    account creation.
  - Separate, explicit consent is obtained before enabling each notification
    channel (WhatsApp, SMS, etc.).
  - Users can withdraw consent at any time by disabling channels or deleting
    their account.

  NOTICE:
  - A clear privacy notice is presented during onboarding, before any data
    collection occurs.
  - The notice specifies: what data is collected, why, how long it is retained,
    and how to exercise rights.

  DATA PRINCIPAL RIGHTS:
  - Right to access: Users can view all their data within the app.
  - Right to correction: Users can edit their profile and task data.
  - Right to erasure: Users can delete individual items or their entire account.
  - Right to grievance redressal: support@unjynx.app responds within 48 hours.
  - Right to nominate: Nomination feature planned for future release.

  DATA FIDUCIARY OBLIGATIONS:
  - Data is collected only for specified purposes (no secondary use).
  - Data accuracy is maintained (users can correct at any time).
  - Data is retained only as long as necessary (see retention table above).
  - Reasonable security safeguards are in place (TLS 1.3, AES-256, etc.).

  CHILDREN'S DATA:
  - UNJYNX is rated "Everyone" / "4+" but does not specifically target children.
  - No data of children under 18 is knowingly processed without verifiable
    parental consent.
  - If we become aware that a child's data has been collected without consent,
    it will be deleted promptly.

  CROSS-BORDER DATA TRANSFER:
  - Primary data processing occurs on self-hosted infrastructure.
  - Third-party SDKs (Sentry, PostHog, RevenueCat) may process data outside
    India. Adequate security measures and contractual safeguards are in place
    per DPDP Act requirements.
  - Users are informed of this in the privacy notice.

  DATA BREACH NOTIFICATION:
  - In the event of a personal data breach, the Data Protection Board of India
    and affected users will be notified within 72 hours.
  - Notification will include: nature of breach, data affected, remedial actions
    taken, and contact information for the Data Protection Officer.

  DATA PROTECTION OFFICER:
  - Contact: dpo@unjynx.app
  - Responsible for: compliance monitoring, breach response, user grievances

  COMPLIANCE DEADLINE:
  - Full compliance targeted before May 2027 (statutory deadline).
  - Current implementation already covers all major requirements.

================================================================================
  10. PLAY STORE DATA SAFETY SECTION PREVIEW
================================================================================

  How this will appear to users on the Play Store:

  DATA SAFETY
  +-----------------------------------------------------------------+
  | Data shared                                                      |
  | No data is shared with third parties                             |
  +-----------------------------------------------------------------+
  | Data collected                                                   |
  | Name, Email address, App activity, Crash logs, Device IDs        |
  +-----------------------------------------------------------------+
  | Security practices                                               |
  | Data is encrypted in transit                                     |
  | You can request that data be deleted                             |
  +-----------------------------------------------------------------+

  Note: While we do share some data with third-party SDKs (Sentry, PostHog,
  RevenueCat), Google's Data Safety guidelines classify "sharing" as providing
  data to third parties for their own purposes. Our SDK data sharing is purely
  for app functionality (crash reporting, analytics, billing) and is therefore
  classified as "collected" rather than "shared" per Google's definitions.
